race.comment: RED SPARKS (7) went forward from the low draw first-up from a spell before fading over 1200m at Colac. She has more to give and is proven second-up. Maps well and should go close. BROMEO (5) settled rearward and almost got up for a likely win at Wangaratta. Draws inside today and keeps the handy 2kg claim. Should be right in it. GOT OUT THE FENCE (2) won at Berrigan by a space and just missed at Swan Hill following. Needs a good ride but is thrown in with the 4kg claim and has to be considered. LITTLE SANDY (6) was unwanted in betting last time but scored by 0.8 lengths over 1200m at Horsham. Likely advantaged by the soft track, but on that effort she can't be ruled out. FREDERICK (1) disappointed at  Werribee over 1408m but had been around the mark prior. Comes back in trip with the blinkers on again and off a low gate. Worth a look.
